📌 Project Overview

This project documents a full hardware upgrade of a MacBook Pro 13-inch (Late 2011) to improve performance and repurpose it as a cybersecurity lab machine.

🔧 Upgrades Performed:
✅ 16GB RAM (2x8GB DDR3 1333MHz)
✅ 512GB 2.5" SATA SSD
✅ A1322 Battery Replacement

🎯 Objective
Extend lifespan of legacy hardware
Improve system performance for virtualization
Build a hands-on cybersecurity lab
Demonstrate real-world IT hardware skills

🧰 Tools & Components

🛠️ Tools
Phillips #00 screwdriver
Tri-wing (Y0) screwdriver
Plastic spudger
Anti-static wrist strap (recommended)

💻 Components
16GB DDR3 1333MHz RAM
2.5" SATA SSD
A1322 Replacement Battery

